, and higher rates of tidal disruptions, compared with\nprevious eccentric migration models which consider constant ~Jupiter radii for\nHJ&WJ progenitors. Coupled thermal-dynamical evolution of eccentric gas-giants\ncan therefore play a key-role in their evolution.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 24 Nov 2021 19:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 18 Apr 2022 12:00:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-05-25"}
