e planetary signals for most of\nthe planets, and by the low signal-to-noise ratios (S/N) of the observations\nfor KELT-21b. Here, we compare our results with the known population of planets\nfor which atmospheric detections have been reported in the literature. We find\nthat the empirical frontier between hot and ultra-hot planets, based on the\ndetection of atomic and ionized species in their atmospheres, can be\nestablished as Teq = 2150 K.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 25 Nov 2021 12:57:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-06-29"}
