al{B}_r$ denote the orientations of $K_{2,r}$ in which\none vertex has out-degree $r$. We show that every $\\cal{B}_r$-free oriented\ngraph having chromatic number at least $(r-1)(s-1)(s-2)+2s+1$ and every\nbikernel-perfect oriented graph with girth $g\\geq 5$ having chromatic number at\nleast $2s^{1+\\frac{4}{g-4}}$ contains every oriented tree on at most $s$\nvertices as an induced subgraph.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 25 Nov 2021 15:05:44 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 22 Sep 2022 06:54:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-23"}
