{"id":"2111.13143","submitter":"Erwin Luesink","authors":"Erwin Luesink and Sagy Ephrati and Paolo Cifani and Bernard Geurts","title":"Casimir preserving stochastic Lie-Poisson integrators","comments":"22 pages, 9 figures, fourth version, all comments are welcome!","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.NA cs.NA","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Casimir preserving integrators for stochastic Lie-Poisson equations with\nStratonovich noise are developed extending Runge-Kutta Munthe-Kaas methods. The\nunderlying Lie-Poisson structure is preserved along stochastic trajectories. A\nrelated stochastic differential equation on the Lie algebra is derived. The\nsolution of this differential equation updates the evolution of the Lie-Poisson\ndynamics by means of the exponential map. The constructed numerical method\nconserves Casimir-invariants exactly, which is important for long time\nintegration. This is illustrated numerically for the case of the stochastic\nheavy top and the stochastic sine-Euler equations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 25 Nov 2021 15:58:21 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 2 Dec 2021 11:03:43 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 3 Dec 2021 15:43:41 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 6 Dec 2021 15:37:42 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Wed, 1 Jun 2022 13:58:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-06-02"}
